[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     77[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe sample cluster candidate in Expected Results confirms the shape. The narrative ("A spatiotemporal cluster of 23 fever-respiratory and ILI ED visits across census tracts 36055-001100 through 36055-001400 over the past 7 days. The observed count is 3.6 times the historical baseline... Cases are demographically skewed toward school-aged children (5-17) who account for 12 of 23 cases. The geographic centroid is within 0.4 miles of three elementary schools serving the affected tracts. Wastewater surveillance from the watershed serving these tracts shows a 1.8x increase in non-pathogen-specific viral RNA concentration over the past 10 days. School-district absenteeism is 18 percent over the past 5 school days, compared to a 5-year baseline of 7.5 percent for this week...") is explicit content that names the affected geographies at census-tract granularity, the demographic skew, the school-district context, and the lab and wastewater context.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     78[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     79[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mTwo recipe-3.10-distinctive amplifications: (1) The line-list-summary aggregates may be re-identifying in small geographies. The recipe correctly addresses this in the Suppressed-Cell-Rules framing ("Counts below the suppression threshold (typically 5 or 10, depending on jurisdiction) cannot be published in geographic detail without re-identification risk"), but the cluster-bus payload doesn't enforce suppression at the publication boundary; the full cluster (with line-list summary at census-tract granularity) flows to all four subscribers regardless of cell counts. The OpenSearch cluster-index specifically is queried by surveillance-leadership and (depending on access policy) cross-jurisdictional partners; suppressing at the index-write boundary rather than at the query boundary is the operationally-correct discipline. (2) The eCR/NEDSS connector sends PHI to external public health authorities under HIPAA's public-health exception; the case-detail data must include patient identifiers for line-list integration, but the cluster-summary payload (the geographies, the demographic distribution, the multi-source concordance) does not need to carry PHI to those external systems beyond the case-by-case eCR submissions. Routing the full cluster (with line-list summary and narrative) into the eCR/NEDSS connector and the cross-jurisdictional notification flow expands the PHI surface beyond what the external integration requires.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     80[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     81[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mSame chapter-3-settled discipline as Recipes 3.1, 3.3, 3.4, 3.5, 3.6, 3.7, 3.8, 3.9: high-fanout notification channels carry the cluster ID only, and the consuming application fetches the full record by ID through an authenticated path so the notification channel never carries PHI. Ninth distinct PHI-minimization-inside-the-BAA surface across the cookbook.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     82[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
