[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    233[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mFor Recipe 3.10 specifically the consequence is calibrated to four pathways: (1) the supervised retraining pathway (doubled label rows on rare positive cases distort class balance for the supervised re-ranker, and confirmed outbreaks are the rarest positive class in any chapter-3 recipe); (2) the cluster-management pathway (duplicate clusters for the same geography-syndrome pair fragment investigations, inflate the surveillance team queue, and break the cluster-grouping intent the recipe explicitly relies on); (3) the notifiable-condition reporting pathway (a redelivered confirmed-outbreak outcome event can initiate the NEDSS or NORS reporting clock twice; state public health statutes specify reporting timelines and a doubled clock initiation produces audit-trail ambiguity that complicates statutory-compliance defense); (4) the cross-jurisdictional notification pathway (duplicate notifications sent to neighboring jurisdictions degrade trust in the federation pattern).[K
