[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    311[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mCross-source geographic crosswalk service.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A first-class service that resolves "for clinical signal at tract T, what sewersheds, school districts, retail pharmacy catchments, and other auxiliary-source geographies cover the same population?" The crosswalk is maintained in Aurora PostGIS (boundary geometries plus relationship tables). The fusion layer queries the crosswalk for each candidate geography and pulls auxiliary-source signals from the related geographies.[K
