[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    422[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLex failover within Connect.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A contact flow branch that triggers when the Lex invocation fails or times out, dropping the call to a DTMF menu within Connect. The DTMF menu is a degraded-but-functional state that handles the highest-volume intents (refill transfer, billing transfer, nurse-line transfer, hours-and-location, operator).[K
